DataValidation.InputMessage: Enter title of this project in cell B2. Information about how to use this worksheet, including instructions for screen readers and the author of this workbook is in the About worksheet. Continue navigating down column A to hear further instructions.
Enter Company Name in cell B4. A legend is in cells I4 through AC4. The Legend label is in cell G4.

Enter the name of the Project Lead in cell B5. Enter the Project Start date in cell C6 or allow the sample formula to find the smallest date value from the Gantt Data table. Project Start Date: label is in cell B6.

A Scrolling Increment is in cell C7. Months for the dates in row 7 are displayed starting in cells I6 through cell BL6. Do not modify these cells. They are auto updated based on the project start date in cell F6.
Cells I9 through BL9 contain the day number of the month for the Month represented in the cell block above each date cell and are auto calculated. Do not modify these cells.
A scrollbar is in cells I8 through BL8. To jump forward or backward in the timeline, enter a value of 0 or higher in cell C7. A value of 0 takes you to the beginning of the chart.

This row contains headers for the project schedule. B9 through G9 contains schedule information. Cells I9 through BL9 contain the first letter of each day of the week for the date above that heading. All project timeline charting is auto generated.

Enter Project information starting in cell B11 through cell G11. Enter Milestone Description, select a Category, assign someone to the task, and enter the progress, start date, and number of days for the task to start charting.
This row marks the end of the Gantt milestone data. DO NOT enter anything in this row. To add more items, insert new rows above this one.
